    <h3 class="bold">Set up your local repository</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Clone the SamuraiDojo repository
            <ul>
                <li><span class="bold">Safelite Developers:</span> <a href="https://github.com/Safelite/SamuraiDojo" target="_blank">https://github.com/Safelite/SamuraiDojo</a></li>
                <li>
                    <span class="bold">Non-Safelite Developers</span> (or if you're having Github issues)
                    <ol>
                        <li>Send your GitHub username to <a href="mailto: shoemaker.277@osu.edu">shoemaker.277@osu.edu</a>. You won't be able to push until I add your username as a collaborator</li>
                        <li>Clone this repository: <a href="https://github.com/mattshoe81/SamuraiDojo.git" target="_blank">https://github.com/mattshoe81/SamuraiDojo.git</a></li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Branch from <code>master</code> (not develop) and name your branch whatever you like. It would be helpful if you stuck with the same branch every week</li>
        <li>Right click the SamuraiDojo.Scoreboard project and select 'Set as Startup Project'</li>
        <li>
            Select/Highlight the SamuraiDojo.ScoreBoard project in the Solution Explorer:
            <ul>
                <li>Click the 'Properties' tab to the right of the solution explorer</li>
                <li>Set Windows Authentication to 'Enabled'</li>
                <li>Set Anonymous Authentication to 'Disabled'</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Go to the SamuraiDojo/Samurai.cs file and add your name.
            <ul>
                <li>NOTE: this must be your 'first.last' windows login</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h3 class="bold">Solve the puzzle!</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Find the current week's puzzle at SamuraiDojo/Battles/Week#</li>
        <li>
            Extend that week's base class and implement the abstract method(s)
            <ul>
                <li>Decorate your class with the <code>[WrittenBy(Samurai.YOU)]</code> attribute</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Extend the base test for the week in SamuraiDojo.Test/Week#
            <ul>
                <li>Decorate your class with the <code>[TestClass]</code> and <code>[WrittenBy(Samurai.YOU)]</code> attributes</li>
                <li>You can run your tests at any time to see how many points you've won</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span class="bold">Important! </span> Make sure you decorate all of your classes with the <code>[WrittenBy(Samurai.YOU)]</code> attribute</li>
    </ol>

    <h3 class="bold">Submit your solution</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Pull request your branch into <code>master</code> (not develop) and request a review from the week's Sensei.
            <ul>
                <li>The week's Sensei is listed on the <a href="/">home</a> page beneath the week's title, above the code section.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

</div>